verbs.description: overmast (third-person singular simple present overmasts, present participle overmasting, simple past and past participle overmasted)

entries.meaning: To furnish with a mast or masts overly tall or heavy.
examples: The double desire of being able to overtake a weaker flying enemy, or to escape when pursued by a stronger, has induced the owners to overmast their cruisers, and to spread too much canvass;  […]
